Olayemi Toviho, popularly known as Obasanjo, has won the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) ticket for Badagry Federal Constituency. The House of Representatives primary election was re-conducted. Toviho had on May 22 won the cancelled primary. On Monday, he polled all the 30 votes cast at the party’s secretariat at Awa Customs Quarters, Badagry. The election started at 5:20 p.m. with 29 delegates from the wards and 1 national delegate, NAN reports. Toviho contested against a businessman, Adekunle Lebile who was not at the venue. Also absent was PDP Chairman in Badagry Local Government Area, Abidemi Akojenu. The Returning Officer, Johnson Avoseh declared Toviho the winner. He described the process as peaceful and transparent. “My victory shows that people of Badagry want me to represent them, and I promise not to disappoint them”, Toviho said. The flagbearer has worked for 16 years at the National Assembly.